headline.main: GREEK SUBMARINES SCORE; Alexander Says They Have Sunk 50,000 Tons of Italian Ships

lead_paragraph: LONDON, Oct. 30 -- Greek submarines operating in the Mediterranean have sunk 50,000 tons of Italian shipping, A.V. Alexander, First Lord of the Admiralty, said today at the meeting of the Anglo-Hellenic League to commemorate the first anniversary of Italy's invasion of Greece.
abstract: On Ital shipping sunk by Greek submarines, s to Anglo-Hellenic League
